Pre-Game Insights: Both Vietnam and Indonesia will eye a comeback in their respective AFC Asian Cup 2023 campaigns.
With both teams losing their first match, either side will look to salvage a comeback, making the contest even more exciting.
Nguyen Van Toan will be the driving force for Vietnam in this clash.
Witan Sulaeman will aim to lead Indonesia to a victory over Vietnam.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be held at Abdullah Bin Khalifa Stadium, Doha on 19th January 2024 at 14:30 GMT.
Indonesia have conceded a goal in each of their last five matches.
The last time these two sides met, Vietnam emerged victorious.
Both the teams have lost their respective AFC Asian Cup 2023 openers.
Others: The predicted lineup for Vietnam is Trieu (GK), Thanh, Binh, Phan, Anh, Trong, Van Thanh, Son Nguyen, Van Toan, Tien Linh, Hai Pham.
The predicted lineup for Indonesia is Ari (GK), Amat, Baggott, Ridho, Sayuri, Hubner, Jenner, Arhan, Ferdinan, Struick, Witan.
The telecast for Vietnam vs Indonesia will be available on various channels including Sports 18, Jio Cinema, FPT Play, MNC Media, BeinSports, Alkass, ADTV, Triller TV, and Network 10.
